1
00:01:39,760 --> 00:01:40,600
I'm back.

2
00:01:40,840 --> 00:01:41,600
Brother Xuan Yu.

3
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,000
Making wallpaper is such a hassle.

4
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,200
We can barely keep up.

5
00:01:44,480 --> 00:01:45,600
I brought some snacks for everyone.

6
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,640
Share them around later.

7
00:01:46,920 --> 00:01:47,680
Xuan Yu.

8
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:48,320
Zhang Du.

9
00:01:48,320 --> 00:01:49,560
Come take a look.

10
00:01:49,640 --> 00:01:51,400
Is this color right?

11
00:01:52,160 --> 00:01:54,200
With your dedication, it's got to be right.

12
00:01:54,680 --> 00:01:55,800
I got this for you.

13
00:01:55,880 --> 00:01:56,680
Thanks.

14
00:01:57,160 --> 00:01:58,000
You're back.

15
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:59,440
Mom.

16
00:02:00,320 --> 00:02:01,880
Set the work aside for a moment.

17
00:02:03,720 --> 00:02:06,280
Uncle, I got this for you.

18
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:08,440
You actually bought it.

19
00:02:08,919 --> 00:02:10,120
Strength 2.00, just like you said.

20
00:02:10,120 --> 00:02:10,960
Try it and see.

21
00:02:11,200 --> 00:02:11,920
Let me try.

22
00:02:15,760 --> 00:02:16,840
This is really nice.

23
00:02:17,400 --> 00:02:18,280
With these,

24
00:02:18,440 --> 00:02:19,840
I can help your mom

25
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,520
with the fine sorting work.

26
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:23,120
Nice one, son.

27
00:02:23,480 --> 00:02:24,720
You've got a heart after all.

28
00:02:24,960 --> 00:02:26,600
You didn't forget about your uncle.

29
00:02:28,080 --> 00:02:30,520
Xuan Yu, go check on your dad.

30
00:02:31,480 --> 00:02:32,560
What's wrong with him now?

31
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:34,200
What happened to your dad?

32
00:02:34,840 --> 00:02:37,640
Ever since you called saying we had orders,

33
00:02:37,640 --> 00:02:40,640
he's been thrilled, leading everyone to work

34
00:02:40,640 --> 00:02:41,840
day and night.

35
00:02:41,840 --> 00:02:43,360
He wouldn't listen to anyone.

36
00:02:43,360 --> 00:02:44,920
Now he's laid up in bed.

37
00:02:45,920 --> 00:02:47,000
The expenses are huge,

38
00:02:48,200 --> 00:02:50,440
and business hasn't really picked up.

39
00:02:50,800 --> 00:02:51,800
He's under a lot of pressure.

40
00:02:52,280 --> 00:02:54,840
When he heard we got wallpaper orders,

41
00:02:54,840 --> 00:02:56,200
how could he not be happy?

42
00:02:57,000 --> 00:02:59,160
Still, we can't just let him tough it out.

43
00:02:59,720 --> 00:03:01,200
We're not ignoring him.

44
00:03:01,640 --> 00:03:03,720
I told him to let Xiao Man look after him.

45
00:03:03,920 --> 00:03:04,720
He wouldn't have it.

46
00:03:04,720 --> 00:03:06,840
Said it would be a waste of manpower.

47
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:09,080
So we agreed

48
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:12,840
that Xiao Man would check on him every hour,

49
00:03:13,080 --> 00:03:14,800
bring him some water,

50
00:03:14,840 --> 00:03:16,280
help him to the bathroom, and so on.

51
00:03:16,280 --> 00:03:17,640
Your dad's getting old.

52
00:03:18,560 --> 00:03:19,800
When people get old,

53
00:03:20,280 --> 00:03:22,080
they're not how they used to be.

54
00:03:22,720 --> 00:03:23,920
When you're young,

55
00:03:24,640 --> 00:03:27,160
you can hold up the sky if it falls.

56
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:28,440
But when you're old,

57
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:31,000
even the tiniest thing

58
00:03:31,360 --> 00:03:32,720
becomes a big deal.

59
00:03:32,840 --> 00:03:33,920
You've got to persuade your dad

60
00:03:34,520 --> 00:03:36,480
to get back surgery at the hospital.

61
00:03:37,520 --> 00:03:39,960
From now on, you need to be more considerate,

62
00:03:40,200 --> 00:03:41,480
and take on more of the burden.

63
00:03:43,920 --> 00:03:45,880
Yiran, you're really amazing.

64
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:47,800
This work will keep us plenty busy.

65
00:03:48,240 --> 00:03:48,960
Sister Yiran.

66
00:03:48,960 --> 00:03:51,040
Bringing back so many big clients this time,

67
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:52,920
Taohua Town is really going to boom.

68
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:54,320
If you keep inflating her ego,

69
00:03:54,320 --> 00:03:55,600
she'll float right up to the sky.

70
00:03:56,800 --> 00:03:57,680
It's mainly thanks to

71
00:03:57,680 --> 00:03:59,680
Director Liao's leadership,

72
00:03:59,680 --> 00:04:00,680
and her guidance.

73
00:04:00,800 --> 00:04:01,960
Flattery.

74
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:04,640
Can't even win you over with sweet words.

75
00:04:06,080 --> 00:04:07,920
One or two firms probably can't handle it all.

76
00:04:08,800 --> 00:04:09,880
How do we divide it?

77
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:12,800
You went through a lot to bring in this business.

78
00:04:12,800 --> 00:04:14,120
Don't let it go to waste now.

79
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,800
I almost forgot until you mentioned it.

80
00:04:15,880 --> 00:04:16,880
Let me show you.

81
00:04:20,560 --> 00:04:21,320
Here, Director Liao.

82
00:04:21,320 --> 00:04:22,200
Take a look.

83
00:04:22,800 --> 00:04:25,080
This is what I drafted for the Xuan Paper Association,

84
00:04:25,080 --> 00:04:27,240
a revised industry code.

85
00:04:27,680 --> 00:04:28,800
Any company willing

86
00:04:28,800 --> 00:04:30,520
to sign the agreement

87
00:04:30,520 --> 00:04:32,200
will get a fair share based

88
00:04:32,200 --> 00:04:33,680
on their production capacity.

89
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:34,440
In that case,

90
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,320
I think Chairman Xiao can handle it.

91
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,600
An industry code.

92
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:42,800
I think that works.

93
00:04:43,360 --> 00:04:44,400
Quite a step forward.

94
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:46,920
Thank you, Director Liao.

95
00:05:00,640 --> 00:05:01,240
Mom.

96
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:02,040
He's asleep.

97
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:02,680
Mom.

98
00:05:03,880 --> 00:05:05,080
Let him sleep a while.

99
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,480
He might not sleep well later.

100
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:09,800
It's hard enough for him to fall asleep.

101
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:13,040
I'm not asleep. I'm awake.

102
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,880
Just lying here all day long.

103
00:05:23,200 --> 00:05:26,200
Can't tell if it's day or night outside.

104
00:05:26,400 --> 00:05:27,600
Sleep if you're tired.

105
00:05:27,760 --> 00:05:29,120
If not, it's time to eat.

106
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,520
How about this, Mom.

107
00:05:30,600 --> 00:05:31,800
I'll bring all the food over.

108
00:05:31,800 --> 00:05:32,680
We'll eat together.

109
00:05:40,360 --> 00:05:41,240
Did you hear that?

110
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,760
Our son knows we should eat as a family.

111
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:48,440
If you ask me...

112
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,320
Xuan Yu's behavior lately...

113
00:05:50,320 --> 00:05:51,440
has been impeccable.

114
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:53,440
Look, ever since you've been bedridden,

115
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:55,240
he's been by your side every day,

116
00:05:55,240 --> 00:05:57,120
never leaving for a minute.

117
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:02,320
Over the years, our Xuan paper industry

118
00:06:02,680 --> 00:06:03,840
hasn't been doing very well.

119
00:06:04,520 --> 00:06:06,000
And now we're facing

120
00:06:06,520 --> 00:06:07,680
this cutthroat competition.

121
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,040
Let's put the past behind us

122
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:09,920
and not bring it up again.

123
00:06:10,560 --> 00:06:13,560
Thanks to the training our leaders gave us,

124
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:14,760
all of us

125
00:06:14,760 --> 00:06:16,320
have gained a much better understanding

126
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:18,360
of business integrity

127
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,920
and laws and regulations.

128
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,440
The Development Office found us

129
00:06:22,440 --> 00:06:23,440
a new livelihood.

130
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:25,120
And this new livelihood

131
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,440
is a golden opportunity.

132
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:27,880
It wasn't easy to come by.

133
00:06:28,320 --> 00:06:31,560
So I hope everyone will truly cherish it.

134
00:06:31,760 --> 00:06:32,560
Alright.

135
00:06:32,560 --> 00:06:33,680
I'll say just one thing.

136
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:35,760
We all share this livelihood,

137
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:37,560
but ruining it for everyone

138
00:06:37,800 --> 00:06:38,920
is something we absolutely cannot do.

139
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:39,760
Understood?

140
00:06:39,760 --> 00:06:40,680
Understood.

141
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:54,440
Why are you sitting way over there?

142
00:06:54,800 --> 00:06:55,920
Isn't that uncomfortable?

143
00:06:56,120 --> 00:06:58,640
It's fine, I'll just grab a few bites.

144
00:06:58,880 --> 00:07:01,000
Come on, sit closer to your dad.

145
00:07:01,000 --> 00:07:02,000
Come here, come on.

146
00:07:27,320 --> 00:07:29,440
We're establishing industry rules

147
00:07:29,440 --> 00:07:32,240
not to make things hard for anyone,

148
00:07:32,320 --> 00:07:35,120
but so we can all progress together

149
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,000
and advance the industry.

150
00:07:37,200 --> 00:07:37,920
Good.

151
00:07:38,000 --> 00:07:40,120
Good, good, good.

152
00:07:41,080 --> 00:07:41,880
I wasn't finished yet.

153
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:42,440
Director,

154
00:07:42,440 --> 00:07:44,360
your speech just now was brilliant.

155
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,560
Especially the ending. Clean and sharp.

156
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:47,920
You flatter me.

157
00:07:48,440 --> 00:07:50,560
This whole thing feels

158
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:52,240
a bit lacking in ceremony.

159
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,520
Not solemn enough, don't you think?

160
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,240
That's my fault, my fault.

161
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,880
Director Liao makes a good point.

162
00:07:56,120 --> 00:07:57,880
We're lacking ceremony today.

163
00:07:57,880 --> 00:07:59,440
We should be like the ancients,

164
00:07:59,440 --> 00:08:01,000
like the Oath of the Peach Garden,

165
00:08:01,000 --> 00:08:02,680
and seal our pact in blood!

166
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:03,800
That's a great idea.

167
00:08:04,320 --> 00:08:05,560
That's a wonderful idea!

168
00:08:05,680 --> 00:08:07,760
We should seal it in blood!

169
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:09,120
Seal it in blood, seal it in blood!

170
00:08:09,120 --> 00:08:10,440
Let's follow the ancients' example,

171
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:11,320
and make it more formal.

172
00:08:11,320 --> 00:08:12,920
That's, that's not really necessary.

173
00:08:13,520 --> 00:08:14,520
Right, right, true.

174
00:08:14,680 --> 00:08:15,640
We don't even have a knife.

175
00:08:15,640 --> 00:08:16,680
How can we seal it in blood?

176
00:08:16,680 --> 00:08:17,400
Director,

177
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,000
will this do?

178
00:08:23,040 --> 00:08:23,680
This works.

179
00:08:23,680 --> 00:08:24,680
Come, Director Liao.

180
00:08:24,800 --> 00:08:25,400
Here.

181
00:08:25,400 --> 00:08:26,000
That works.

182
00:08:26,000 --> 00:08:26,640
Come on.

183
00:08:27,800 --> 00:08:31,560
This, this isn't really appropriate.

184
00:08:31,560 --> 00:08:33,520
It's not those times anymore, look.

185
00:08:33,559 --> 00:08:35,440
Director Liao is so considerate.

186
00:08:39,240 --> 00:08:40,559
Director Liao just said it too,

187
00:08:40,559 --> 00:08:43,320
our new rules are all set.

188
00:08:43,360 --> 00:08:47,000
If anyone breaks them in the future,

189
00:08:47,080 --> 00:08:49,080
we'll handle it strictly

190
00:08:49,080 --> 00:08:50,160
according to the new rules.

191
00:08:50,160 --> 00:08:50,680
All right?

192
00:08:50,680 --> 00:08:51,320
Good, good.

193
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:52,000
Good, come on.

194
00:08:52,000 --> 00:08:53,120
Let's sign.

195
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:04,920
Dad,

196
00:09:07,960 --> 00:09:10,880
please go to the hospital for treatment.

197
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:13,000
If not for yourself,

198
00:09:13,360 --> 00:09:16,240
then do it for Mom and me.

199
00:09:18,280 --> 00:09:19,240
If I go,

200
00:09:22,200 --> 00:09:24,680
what will happen to this mess?

201
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:28,520
Dad,

202
00:09:29,120 --> 00:09:30,240
are you worried

203
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,800
the factory can't keep going?

204
00:09:31,920 --> 00:09:34,320
You don't know how hard it is to get by.

205
00:09:34,440 --> 00:09:35,960
That order from Beijing

206
00:09:36,480 --> 00:09:38,480
won't hold us over for long.

207
00:09:39,160 --> 00:09:41,000
If we can't sell the paper and get cash,

208
00:09:41,080 --> 00:09:42,680
we can't pay wages,

209
00:09:43,640 --> 00:09:45,360
and the factory will surely collapse.

210
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,800
The Xuan family's century-old business will end with me.

211
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,560
I have a way to sell all

212
00:09:49,560 --> 00:09:50,560
your stockpiled paper.

213
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:55,560
Just promise me you'll get the surgery.

214
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,160
I'll do whatever it takes to sell that stock,

215
00:09:59,160 --> 00:10:00,280
and even fetch a good price.

216
00:10:04,520 --> 00:10:05,600
I believe you, I believe you.

217
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,640
My son can sell it, I believe it.

218
00:10:08,120 --> 00:10:09,520
But one thing though,

219
00:10:10,280 --> 00:10:11,760
don't ask how I do it.

220
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,280
You can't do anything shady.

221
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:19,520
Dad, I wouldn't break the law, would I?

222
00:10:26,040 --> 00:10:27,800
What are you standing there for?

223
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:30,040
Just trust what your son says.

224
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,960
Do whatever he tells you to do.

225
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,000
All right, let's eat first,

226
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:38,040
then I'll call the hospital,

227
00:10:38,040 --> 00:10:40,000
and have a car take Dad there.

228
00:10:40,000 --> 00:10:41,520
After dinner, I'll pack our things

229
00:10:41,680 --> 00:10:43,040
and go to the hospital with your dad.

230
00:10:43,400 --> 00:10:45,520
I'm leaving things here to you.

231
00:10:45,760 --> 00:10:46,320
Okay.

232
00:10:59,000 --> 00:10:59,840
So much.

233
00:11:01,880 --> 00:11:02,880
Over the years,

234
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:05,160
your dad refused to lay off workers,

235
00:11:05,800 --> 00:11:07,920
worried they'd have no work or income.

236
00:11:08,120 --> 00:11:09,800
So more and more paper piled up.

237
00:11:10,120 --> 00:11:11,240
And sales weren't good either.

238
00:11:11,480 --> 00:11:13,160
So it all ended up stacked here.

239
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:15,000
Don't worry.

240
00:11:15,280 --> 00:11:16,640
Our Xuan family's paper,

241
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,040
has flawless quality.

242
00:11:19,960 --> 00:11:20,880
Here's what we'll do, Uncle.

243
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:23,680
Have everyone set aside their current work.

244
00:11:23,680 --> 00:11:25,400
On all the packaging for this paper,

245
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,600
stamp two words:

246
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:27,200
"Out-of-Print."

247
00:11:27,200 --> 00:11:28,800
I've already got someone making the stamp.

248
00:11:28,800 --> 00:11:30,000
It's on its way here.

249
00:11:30,680 --> 00:11:31,560
Out-of-print?

250
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:33,520
Whose paper is going out of print?

251
00:11:34,320 --> 00:11:36,360
I'm just doing a count first,

252
00:11:36,360 --> 00:11:37,280
to get a rough idea.

253
00:11:37,560 --> 00:11:39,320
We'll talk about it in detail later.

254
00:11:40,280 --> 00:11:41,960
Alright, I'm off then.

255
00:11:41,960 --> 00:11:42,480
Okay.

256
00:11:47,720 --> 00:11:48,920
Tell me the truth, Xuan Yu.

257
00:11:48,920 --> 00:11:50,280
Is Master really okay or not?

258
00:11:51,000 --> 00:11:51,960
Nothing serious.

259
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:54,120
But even after his back heals, he can't scoop paper anymore.

260
00:11:54,120 --> 00:11:55,160
He can't do heavy labor.

261
00:11:55,520 --> 00:11:57,040
So all the paper he made before,

262
00:11:57,040 --> 00:11:58,480
has now become out-of-print paper.

263
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,040
You're a big boss now.

264
00:12:00,360 --> 00:12:02,000
Can't you smell the business opportunity here?

265
00:12:03,360 --> 00:12:04,360
What opportunity?

266
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:07,520
Anyone who knows Xuan paper knows this:

267
00:12:07,520 --> 00:12:09,000
top-tier paper is like top-tier liquor.

268
00:12:09,520 --> 00:12:10,640
The older it gets, the more valuable it is.

269
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:12,720
Who doesn't stash away a few boxes of old paper?

270
00:12:13,160 --> 00:12:13,960
Think about it.

271
00:12:14,320 --> 00:12:16,200
The Xuan family, a millennium-old paper dynasty,

272
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:17,760
their 35th-generation heir,

273
00:12:17,760 --> 00:12:21,200
a master inheritor's out-of-print paper.

274
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,520
Wouldn't that fetch a great price?

275
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:31,080
It's out-of-print paper, Xuan Yu.

276
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,520
Have you ever thought

277
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:33,920
if we actually do this,

278
00:12:33,920 --> 00:12:35,080
what the consequences will be?

279
00:12:35,160 --> 00:12:36,400
People out there might question

280
00:12:36,400 --> 00:12:37,400
the Xuan family's reputation.

281
00:12:39,480 --> 00:12:40,600
In my dad's heart,

282
00:12:41,440 --> 00:12:43,600
keeping the paper mill alive matters most.

283
00:12:44,040 --> 00:12:45,520
If the paper mill goes under,

284
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,520
the craft dies with it.

285
00:12:47,840 --> 00:12:49,120
If we don't fix this problem,

286
00:12:49,360 --> 00:12:50,880
my dad won't rest easy while recovering.

287
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,360
But you can't just exploit your dad.

288
00:12:53,360 --> 00:12:54,880
He's your own father.

289
00:12:54,880 --> 00:12:55,720
I know.

290
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,640
Brother Min, I know you care about my dad.

291
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,280
Don't you think I do too?

292
00:13:00,920 --> 00:13:02,600
This is the best solution

293
00:13:02,600 --> 00:13:04,080
I can come up with right now.

294
00:13:04,600 --> 00:13:05,920
If you really care about my dad,

295
00:13:05,920 --> 00:13:06,840
just name your price.

296
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:08,880
Let's keep the profits in the family.

297
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:15,000
Don't drag me into this.

298
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,680
Every time, I end up being the sucker.

299
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:19,480
If this really goes wrong this time,

300
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:21,240
Master will break my legs.

301
00:13:21,600 --> 00:13:22,200
Brother Min,

302
00:13:22,200 --> 00:13:23,520
be fair, alright?

303
00:13:23,520 --> 00:13:23,880
Me,

304
00:13:23,880 --> 00:13:25,440
when have I ever shortchanged you?

305
00:13:25,440 --> 00:13:26,440
Take last time, for example.

306
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:28,000
Did I make you spend a single cent?

307
00:13:28,480 --> 00:13:29,760
And in the end, didn't you come out ahead?

308
00:13:29,760 --> 00:13:31,360
Even Master and his wife praised you.

309
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:35,240
So, you've got to cooperate with me.

310
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,760
We need to figure out a way

311
00:13:36,760 --> 00:13:39,640
to clear out this out-of-print paper fast.

312
00:13:41,880 --> 00:13:43,360
You, you're really something.

313
00:13:44,040 --> 00:13:45,840
You've got a knife to my throat now.

314
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:46,520
Right?

315
00:13:46,640 --> 00:13:48,120
Give me a straight answer. In or out?

316
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,160
I'm in,

317
00:13:56,240 --> 00:13:57,520
but Master can't find out.

318
00:13:58,640 --> 00:13:59,440
Here's the plan.

319
00:14:00,760 --> 00:14:01,640
I'll drop the news

320
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:04,040
into my industry chat groups.

321
00:14:04,720 --> 00:14:06,240
Once I post it, those groups will explode.

322
00:14:06,600 --> 00:14:07,760
Paper will fly out,

323
00:14:08,200 --> 00:14:09,320
and money will pour in.

324
00:14:10,480 --> 00:14:11,880
But my price is going to be high.

325
00:14:12,240 --> 00:14:13,840
Anything lower and I won't agree.

326
00:14:14,000 --> 00:14:14,880
The quantity is huge too.

327
00:14:15,400 --> 00:14:16,200
No, that won't work.

328
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:19,120
Rarity drives value.

329
00:14:19,280 --> 00:14:20,760
Too much and it loses its worth.

330
00:14:20,760 --> 00:14:21,640
So,

331
00:14:21,720 --> 00:14:23,640
outsiders can't know how much stock we have.

332
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:25,760
The two of us need to plan this carefully.

333
00:14:26,640 --> 00:14:28,120
You're the master planner.

334
00:14:28,520 --> 00:14:30,640
Whatever you say goes, alright?

335
00:14:33,040 --> 00:14:35,040
First, post the message in the groups.

336
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:37,280
Makes sense.

337
00:14:38,040 --> 00:14:40,000
But how exactly to post it,

338
00:14:41,120 --> 00:14:42,640
now that's an art form.

339
00:15:02,680 --> 00:15:04,720
Good, good, good.

340
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:07,280
Mr. Tao, your calligraphy is more magnificent than ever.

341
00:15:07,280 --> 00:15:08,440
More and more perfect.

342
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:10,280
This paper is fine, really fine.

343
00:15:10,280 --> 00:15:11,240
Truly excellent.

344
00:15:12,400 --> 00:15:13,880
It captures the essence of heaven and earth.

345
00:15:13,880 --> 00:15:15,960
I came to you because I trust you.

346
00:15:15,960 --> 00:15:17,600
So you better not mess this up for me.

347
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:19,640
This paper really is something.

348
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:20,560
Right, right, right.

349
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,120
I told you, this isn't ordinary paper.

350
00:15:22,120 --> 00:15:23,400
Not ordinary paper at all.

351
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,000
Out-of-print paper.

352
00:15:27,600 --> 00:15:28,640
That's why I'm saying,

353
00:15:28,840 --> 00:15:30,880
whoever grabs this chance will get rich.

354
00:15:31,120 --> 00:15:32,120
Auction? An auction is out of the question.

355
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,200
Absolutely no auction.

356
00:15:33,600 --> 00:15:34,560
Do you understand?

357
00:15:35,880 --> 00:15:37,280
Sell it to those who appreciate it.

358
00:15:37,440 --> 00:15:38,560
If someone doesn't understand paper,

359
00:15:38,560 --> 00:15:39,920
I won't accept any amount they offer.

360
00:15:40,640 --> 00:15:41,760
I'm leaving this matter to you.

361
00:15:41,760 --> 00:15:42,520
Got it.

362
00:15:44,040 --> 00:15:44,880
Mr. Xiao!

363
00:15:46,040 --> 00:15:47,000
You scared me!

364
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,600
What's up?

365
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,840
That's not cool, man.

366
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:49,880
After all these years together,

367
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:51,000
you're hiding something from me.

368
00:15:51,120 --> 00:15:51,960
What am I hiding?

369
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:53,200
I heard everything.

370
00:15:53,200 --> 00:15:54,040
Your phone call.

371
00:15:55,000 --> 00:15:56,240
I've got urgent business here.

372
00:15:57,280 --> 00:15:58,600
What, what was that,

373
00:15:58,640 --> 00:16:00,280
about not selling even if they pay?

374
00:16:00,280 --> 00:16:01,400
What kind of special paper is it?

375
00:16:01,400 --> 00:16:02,760
You heard wrong, heard wrong.

376
00:16:04,800 --> 00:16:05,800
Let go, let go.

377
00:16:05,800 --> 00:16:06,800
I've got urgent business.

378
00:16:07,640 --> 00:16:08,280
Me...

379
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:09,520
You've definitely got something good going on.

380
00:16:09,520 --> 00:16:10,200
Otherwise, you wouldn't have

381
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:11,480
posted a message in the group today

382
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:12,480
and retracted it three seconds later.

383
00:16:12,480 --> 00:16:14,600
Someone asked me what "out-of-print paper" meant.

384
00:16:18,840 --> 00:16:20,240
Trade secret.

385
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:24,120
I get it.

386
00:16:24,600 --> 00:16:26,640
Tonight I'll bring a good bottle to your place.

387
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:27,000
No, no, no.

388
00:16:27,000 --> 00:16:28,120
Come on, we'll drink until we drop.

389
00:16:28,120 --> 00:16:29,920
Old Fei can't find out about this.

390
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:30,880
I won't, I won't tell anyone.

391
00:16:30,880 --> 00:16:32,000
Just share it with me.

392
00:16:32,040 --> 00:16:33,240
You won't tell anyone else?

393
00:16:33,240 --> 00:16:33,760
Not a word.

394
00:16:33,760 --> 00:16:34,480
You sure?

395
00:16:34,640 --> 00:16:36,120
I promise. You know how you are...

396
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:37,360
Don't worry.

397
00:16:37,400 --> 00:16:38,280
Alright, fine.

398
00:16:38,360 --> 00:16:39,160
See you tonight then.

399
00:16:39,160 --> 00:16:39,640
Great, great.

400
00:16:39,640 --> 00:16:40,480
You can't let anyone know.

401
00:16:40,480 --> 00:16:41,360
Don't worry.

402
00:16:42,360 --> 00:16:44,760
In Taohua Town, my lips are the most sealed.

403
00:16:49,760 --> 00:16:50,760
What chairman?

404
00:16:51,480 --> 00:16:52,440
I'm not your chairman.

405
00:16:52,640 --> 00:16:54,680
Keep it a secret!

406
00:16:54,680 --> 00:16:55,400
How come now the whole town,

407
00:16:55,400 --> 00:16:56,640
everyone in town knows?

408
00:16:56,800 --> 00:16:58,480
Chairman Xiao, I don't know either.

409
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:00,040
I only told you.

410
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:01,120
You... you don't even know?

411
00:17:01,160 --> 00:17:02,040
Let me tell you,

412
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,200
the chance to strike it rich is gone.

413
00:17:03,440 --> 00:17:04,560
Come on, Chairman Xiao.

414
00:17:04,599 --> 00:17:06,560
Are you home? I'll come apologize.

415
00:17:06,560 --> 00:17:07,280
No, no, no.

416
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:08,400
I'm not home.

417
00:17:08,640 --> 00:17:10,680
My front door is jammed with people.

418
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,079
I'm hiding out at Xuan Yu's place now.

419
00:17:12,760 --> 00:17:14,280
Okay, I'll come find you right away.

420
00:17:14,720 --> 00:17:15,599
Don't come!

421
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,319
The moment you show up, I'm leaving.

422
00:17:17,319 --> 00:17:18,200
I don't want to see you.

423
00:17:19,640 --> 00:17:20,920
The big boss sure has style.

424
00:17:21,160 --> 00:17:22,000
So classy.

425
00:17:23,520 --> 00:17:24,839
Come, have some tea, tea, tea.

426
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:36,520
Everything's ready. We're just waiting for the final piece.

427
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:40,080
She's here.

428
00:17:40,080 --> 00:17:41,720
Why didn't you tell me in advance?

429
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:42,840
Didn't she tell you she was coming?

430
00:17:42,840 --> 00:17:44,000
You two chat every day.

431
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:44,720
Quick, quick, quick!

432
00:17:44,720 --> 00:17:45,680
Swap them for new ones!

433
00:17:45,680 --> 00:17:46,240
Hurry up!

434
00:17:47,280 --> 00:17:47,640
Careful, careful.

435
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,240
There's water here, water!

436
00:17:48,240 --> 00:17:49,120
Careful, careful, careful!

437
00:17:49,120 --> 00:17:49,880
I see it.

438
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,640
Chairman Xiao, you're here too.

439
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,880
I've been waiting for you.

440
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:54,120
Thank you, Chairman Xiao.

441
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,480
Sorry to trouble you again, Chairman Xiao.

442
00:17:57,480 --> 00:17:58,360
Don't mention it.

443
00:17:58,640 --> 00:18:00,000
Your share has been set aside for you.

444
00:18:00,040 --> 00:18:01,520
Same price as before.

445
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:04,760
That's great.

446
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:06,120
But, Mr. Xuan,

447
00:18:06,120 --> 00:18:08,760
this time you can't use me as your shield.

448
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,240
The old master wasn't pleased with me last time.

449
00:18:12,240 --> 00:18:13,720
This time, I'm the one calling the shots.

450
00:18:13,720 --> 00:18:15,640
Everything is under control.

451
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:23,920
Brother Xiao.

452
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,120
I know, I know.

453
00:18:25,120 --> 00:18:26,600
Hey, Old Xiao.

454
00:18:26,600 --> 00:18:27,040
Look at this.

455
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:27,920
There's no avoiding them.

456
00:18:27,920 --> 00:18:28,840
Told him not to come, but he had to.

457
00:18:28,840 --> 00:18:30,160
Look at what you've done.

458
00:18:30,240 --> 00:18:31,880
Chairman Xiao, what's going on here?

459
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:32,600
What's the matter with you?

460
00:18:32,600 --> 00:18:33,160
What?

461
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,200
Wasn't this supposed to be confidential?

462
00:18:34,200 --> 00:18:36,560
Old Xiao, this isn't right, is it?

463
00:18:36,560 --> 00:18:37,520
That's not cool of you.

464
00:18:37,520 --> 00:18:38,200
Right, right.

465
00:18:38,200 --> 00:18:38,720
That's not friendly at all.

466
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:39,200
Exactly.

467
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,680
Why didn't you tell me what was going on?

468
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,240
It's not that I won't help you.

469
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,920
I really have no choice.

470
00:18:44,240 --> 00:18:45,440
You all know my master's temper.

471
00:18:45,560 --> 00:18:46,680
You know how he is.

472
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:48,160
If he later sees his out-of-print paper

473
00:18:48,160 --> 00:18:49,520
being sold in Taohua Town,

474
00:18:49,760 --> 00:18:50,800
wouldn't he be furious?

475
00:18:51,080 --> 00:18:52,720
So I told Xuan Yu,

476
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:53,920
we've already agreed on this.

477
00:18:53,920 --> 00:18:56,400
This paper cannot be sold in Taohua Town.

478
00:18:56,400 --> 00:18:58,280
Old Xiao, don't worry about that.

479
00:18:58,280 --> 00:19:00,440
We can help them sell it elsewhere.

480
00:19:00,440 --> 00:19:01,200
Right.

481
00:19:02,040 --> 00:19:03,240
So we'll buy it,

482
00:19:03,240 --> 00:19:04,400
and we won't display it.

483
00:19:04,400 --> 00:19:05,160
We'll keep it hidden.

484
00:19:05,160 --> 00:19:06,400
We'll just collect it, okay?

485
00:19:06,400 --> 00:19:07,240
We'll just collect it.

486
00:19:07,240 --> 00:19:09,600
Yes, yes, this paper is indeed excellent.

487
00:19:09,600 --> 00:19:11,000
But the price is high.

488
00:19:11,000 --> 00:19:12,960
Can any of you actually afford it?

489
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:15,440
Come on, a high price is only fair.

490
00:19:15,440 --> 00:19:17,000
Look at whose craftsmanship it is.

491
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,960
If it were cheap, we wouldn't even want it.

492
00:19:18,960 --> 00:19:20,440
Exactly, right.

493
00:19:20,520 --> 00:19:22,000
Who would want it if it were cheap?

494
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,920
I understand what everyone is thinking.

495
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:26,680
Whether you want to act as middlemen,

496
00:19:26,720 --> 00:19:28,440
or keep it for your own collection,

497
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,280
you all want a share of the profit.

498
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:34,040
I understand, and it's perfectly normal.

499
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,400
But you've all truly come too late.

500
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,040
Dayazhai's capabilities

501
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:40,280
are clear for all to see.

502
00:19:40,840 --> 00:19:42,440
In doing business,

503
00:19:42,520 --> 00:19:44,320
first come, first served, right?

504
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,000
I have to abide by that rule, don't I?

505
00:19:46,400 --> 00:19:47,920
Sorry, everyone.

506
00:19:48,160 --> 00:19:49,440
Our Dayazhai

507
00:19:49,440 --> 00:19:52,280
is about to release high-end bound books.

508
00:19:52,440 --> 00:19:54,200
Master Xuan's out-of-print paper

509
00:19:54,200 --> 00:19:56,680
is perfect timing for us.

510
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:57,920
Business is business.

511
00:19:58,080 --> 00:19:59,640
I shouldn't say too much.

512
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:02,800
But I bet the price Dayazhai is offering,

513
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:03,960
none of you,

514
00:20:05,080 --> 00:20:05,920
can afford to match.

515
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:09,480
Mr. Xin,

516
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:11,480
Aren't you being a bit harsh?

517
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:13,840
A starved camel is bigger than a horse.

518
00:20:13,840 --> 00:20:16,000
Besides, we've been in business for years.

519
00:20:16,920 --> 00:20:17,680
Exactly.

520
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:20,280
Business is tough these days,

521
00:20:20,680 --> 00:20:23,000
but the folks standing behind me,

522
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:24,440
back when paper was expensive,

523
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,760
none of us failed to rake it in.

524
00:20:26,760 --> 00:20:27,480
Right?

525
00:20:27,480 --> 00:20:29,520
Right, exactly.

526
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,880
None of us are short on cash.

527
00:20:30,880 --> 00:20:31,760
Right.

528
00:20:32,800 --> 00:20:33,600
Xuan Yu.

529
00:20:34,560 --> 00:20:35,880
Why don't you reconsider?

530
00:20:36,520 --> 00:20:39,160
The paper is Taohua Town's paper, after all.

531
00:20:39,680 --> 00:20:41,680
So everyone wanting a piece of the pie

532
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:42,840
is perfectly understandable.

533
00:20:42,840 --> 00:20:43,560
Right?

534
00:20:43,560 --> 00:20:44,200
Yeah.

535
00:20:44,200 --> 00:20:44,520
Exactly.

536
00:20:44,520 --> 00:20:45,240
Right, right, that's it.

537
00:20:45,240 --> 00:20:45,760
Yeah.

538
00:20:45,760 --> 00:20:46,480
Yeah, yeah.

539
00:20:46,480 --> 00:20:47,120
You should share at least a little.

540
00:20:47,120 --> 00:20:48,960
Everyone wants a share, right?

541
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,160
Right, exactly.

542
00:20:50,680 --> 00:20:51,480
Mr. Xin,

543
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:54,000
cut us some slack.

544
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:56,920
Just spare a little for everyone.

545
00:21:01,440 --> 00:21:02,000
Alright.

546
00:21:02,560 --> 00:21:03,440
Let me make the call.

547
00:21:03,960 --> 00:21:05,720
Here's the thing, Xin Ran.

548
00:21:06,080 --> 00:21:07,960
Talk to your chairman later.

549
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,080
Ask for less.

550
00:21:09,200 --> 00:21:11,400
Free up some to share with them.

551
00:21:11,520 --> 00:21:12,400
Once you've got the paper,

552
00:21:12,520 --> 00:21:13,240
if you need cash urgently,

553
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,520
sell it out of town for me.

554
00:21:14,840 --> 00:21:16,680
If you're keeping any, hide it well.

555
00:21:16,680 --> 00:21:17,760
Don't let my dad find out.

556
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:20,160
Brother Min.

557
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:21,800
Tomorrow, get a headcount.

558
00:21:21,840 --> 00:21:23,440
Take everyone's names.

559
00:21:23,880 --> 00:21:25,000
Don't make a scene here.

560
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:25,640
People who don't know

561
00:21:25,640 --> 00:21:26,920
might think something happened here.

562
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:27,640
How about this.

563
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,440
Tomorrow, come to the association.

564
00:21:29,640 --> 00:21:31,080
Tell me how much paper you want.

565
00:21:31,080 --> 00:21:32,280
Alright, alright, alright.

566
00:21:32,440 --> 00:21:33,320
It's settled then.

567
